# SchemaTemplateCreatesFields — RETIRED (CUX-09)
#
# Field fan-out for SchemaTemplate/apply was previously declared here but had
# two unfixable bugs:
#   1. The when clause used `=> [ ok: ?template ]` (literal-field syntax) instead
#      of `=> ok(...)` (variant syntax), so the sync never fired.
#   2. The then clause used `?fields.<key>` dot-access on an array, which the sync
#      grammar cannot iterate — the grammar supports fixed-key dot-access on objects
#      only, not variable-length array fan-out.
#
# Because the sync grammar has no mechanism for iterating a variable-length array
# returned in a completion output, the fan-out has been moved into the
# SchemaTemplate/apply handler itself (handlers/ts/app/schema-template.handler.ts).
# The handler uses mapBindings + traverse to write one 'field' relation entry per
# entry in the template's fields JSON array, matching the storage contract of
# FieldDefinition/create (key: `${schema}::${fieldId}`).
#
# This file is retained as an archive placeholder so that the suite manifest entry
# still resolves. The suite manifest entry can be removed if desired — the file
# parses as an empty sync list.
